<percentage>0</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum></teachingTypesInCurriculumYear><track><trackDescription xml:lang="nl"></trackDescription><trackId><![CDATA[47]]></trackId><trackName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Politieke theorie en politiek gedrag]]></trackName><trackType><![CDATA[regular]]></trackType></track><track><trackDescription xml:lang="nl"></trackDescription><trackId><![CDATA[48]]></trackId><trackName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Bestuur en beleid]]></trackName><trackName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Bestuur en beleid]]></trackName><trackType><![CDATA[regular]]></trackType></track><track><trackDescription xml:lang="nl"></trackDescription><trackId><![CDATA[49]]></trackId><trackName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Internationale betrekkingen]]></trackName><trackName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Internationale betrekkingen]]></trackName><trackType><![CDATA[regular]]></trackType></track></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Na de master kun je kiezen voor een carrière aan de universiteit, bij de overheid of in het bedrijfsleven.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Binnen de master Politicologie kun je je specialiseren in een van de volgende trajecten:

* Bestuur en Beleid bestudeert de manier waarop maatschappelijke processen verlopen en hoe hier op legitieme wijze ‘sturing' aan kan worden gegeven.

* Politieke theorie en politiek gedrag bestudeert de verhouding tussen hoe mensen zich - individueel en collectief - in politiek opzicht zouden moeten gedragen en wat zij echt doen.

* Internationale betrekkingen / International Relations
bestudeert sociale conflicten, waarvan aard, oorzaken en gevolgen nationale grenzen overschrijden, waardoor oplossingen niet meer gezocht kunnen worden binnen de kaders van de lokale of nationale politiek.

* Conflict Resolution and Governance provides students with a foundation which will allow them to develop a theoretically informed understanding of shifts in the character and significance of conflicts, consider possibilities for action in real-life situations, and transform conflict into a resource for democratic governance.

* European Union in a Global Order is a research-oriented programme that provides students with a theoretical and empirical understanding of the EU's external relations.]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Politicologie]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[De master politicologie biedt een wetenschappelijke verdieping op de bachelor Politicologie en andere verwante bachelors.]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[beleid]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[conflicten]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[governance]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[oorlog]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[politiek]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[staatsinrichting]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[overheid]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[terrorisme]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[policies]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[conflict]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[governance]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[war]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[politics]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[politics]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[government]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[terrorism]]></searchword><webLink xml:lang="nl">http://www.studeren.uva.nl/ma-politicologie</webLink></programDescriptions><programInternationalization><ErasmusMundusProgram>0</ErasmusMundusProgram><facilitationForeignScholarships>0</facilitationForeignScholarships><foreignStay>0</foreignStay><languageRequirement><languageExam>CPE</languageExam><minimumScore>C1</minimumScore></languageRequirement><languageRequirement><languageExam>IELTS overall band</languageExam><minimumScore>6.5</minimumScore></languageRequirement><languageRequirement><languageExam>TOEFL paper based</languageExam><minimumScore>600</minimumScore></languageR